			border-top: 1px solid rgb(220,220,220);
			font-size: 0.875em;
			margin: 3em 0;
			padding-top: 2em;
		}
	</style>
</head>
<body>
	<h1>Mock Response</h1>
	<p>Sometimes in the course of development you may need to mock http errors. This is a simple service to return various HTTP errors.</p>
	<p>To call each error, simply append the response that you would like returned to the end of this sites URL, like so:</p>
	<code>http://mock.isssues.com/{RESPONSE}</code>
	<p>These responses are supported and can be called via <strong>GET</strong> or <strong>POST</strong>.</p>
	<table cellspacing="0">
		<thead>
			<tr>
				<th>Status</th>
				<th>Description</th>
			</tr>
		</thead>
		<tbody>
			<% @codes.each_pair do |code, description| %>
				<tr>
					<td><strong><%= code %></strong></td>
					<td><%= description %></td>
				</tr>
			<% end %>
			<tr>
				<td><strong>timeout</strong></td>
				<td>Waits 30 seconds before returning successfully.</td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td><strong>hesitate</strong></td>
				<td>Waits 5 seconds before returning successfully.</td>
			</tr>
		</tbody>
	</table>
	<p>If something is missing, drop us a line at hello@isssues.com.</p>
